				\begin{document}$$\mu $$\end{document}μ is the birth/mortality rate (or immigration/emigration rate; for childhood infections, individuals leave the group at a certain age). The recovered individuals are assumed to be immune to the disease. In this particular model setup, the equality of the birth and mortality rates ensures the conservation of the total population density, i.e. N is constant. A simpler version of this model without vaccination was first published in Kermack (1927); (1932; 1933).

