				\begin{document}$$u\in {\mathbb {R}}$$\end{document}u∈R is a parameter). Between the switching moments, a trajectory of the system is an integral curve of a particular vector field. The Preisach operator imposes non-trivial rules for switching from one vector field to another. Some intuition can be drawn from dynamics of systems with dry friction such as models of presliding friction behavior (Al-Bender et al. 2004; Ruderman 2011), and population models with thresholds (Meza and Bhaya 2009).

